Company Description




Repeatedly voted one of Montreal’s Top Employers and Employer of the Year for the 2022 Mercuriades Awards, Rodeo FX is a high-end creative company offering services in visual effects, advertising, animation, and experiential.




Nominated for 3 Emmy® Awards for its work on the series Stranger Things season 4, The Witcher season 2 and Foundation season 1, the independent, Oscar®-winning company boasts close to 800 artists.




Rodeo FX is a creative partner to the world’s best storytellers including Netflix, HBO, Disney, Marvel, Amazon Studios, Warner Bros. and Sony, and has collaborated on ads for YouTube, NBC and Apple. Current projects include Fantastic Beasts: The Secrets of Dumbledore, Resident Evil, Halo, and Stranger Things season 4. Recently released projects include Dune, Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings, WandaVision and The Witcher season 2, all earning nominations at the 2022 VES awards.




Work arrangements:




As a company founded and led by an artist, it is creativity above all that guides us. Our mission is to provide our talents with the freedom and resources they need to deliver quality work and thrive in a stimulating, caring environment. This is why we offer a flexible, hybrid and remote work structure in all our locations.




Job Description




The Pipeline Developer develops tools and solutions in order to optimize the production workflow and to ensure advances in the Rodeo FX pipeline to produce visual effects that meet the studio’s high quality standards.




Main responsibilities:




Create verifiable, effective, and reusable tools using best software development practices;
Develop pipeline tools to for in-house applications and also for software such as Maya, Houdini and Katana, ensuring that they meet departmental standards as requested by supervisors and/or heads of department;
Participate in the complete software development lifecycle, including requirements gathering, designing, supporting and maintaining software;
Create and communicate documentation on the tools developed and provide training to other users;
Perform quality control on work before submitting it for review/approval, ensuring all technical specifications are met, and integrate comments from peer review;
Keep the project team and/or the Head of Pipeline informed of the status of work, issues to be resolved, ramifications of problems encountered and recommend potential solutions;
Ensure deadlines are met, advising the project team promptly if delays could be expected.
Qualifications




Minimum of 3 years of experience working in VFX Pipelines;
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or other related field, or equivalent experience;
Proficient with Python 2.x/3.x and/or C++;
Good knowledge of Nuke, Houdini, Maya or Katana;
Experience working on scripts and command line applications (Unix);
Good understanding of Linux operating system;
Strong skills in debugging and development tests;
Able to communicate solutions to issues in a clear and concise manner;
Excellent sense of prioritization and respect of deadlines.




Additional Information




Full-time, Permanent Contract ;
Flexible, hybrid and remote work structure in all our locations ;
5 paid sick/personal days ;
2 additional statutory holidays in the winter holidays ;
Group Insurance, access to Dialogue online support and to an Employee Assistance Program (EAP) ;
RRSP with employer contribution.




